== Italian ==
/ˌʈʃerkjobottˈista/<br/>
''Noun or adjective, m. or f.''<br/>
Plural: ''cerchiobottisti'' (m) or ''cerchiobottiste'' (f)

From the words [[cerchio]] and [[botte]]. ''Cerchiobottista'' comes from the phrase ''dare un colpo al cerchio e uno alla botte'', or ''to hit once the circle and once the barrel''.

The phrase is used to describe the attitude, in an argument, of agreeing with one position, only to admit that an opposing opinion is also right, never taking a clear stand. It has a generally negative connotation.

